[0m[49m[39m  101,  93[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  102,  94[0m:[39m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[39m  103,  95[0m:[39m[49m rekognition_client = boto3.client("rekognition", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[39m  104,  96[0m:[39m[49m s3_client = boto3.client("s3", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[39m  105,  97[0m:[39m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb")
[0m[49m[39m  106,  98[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  107,  99[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  108, 100[0m:[39m[49m def validate_verification_image(bucket: str, key: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[39m  109, 101[0m:[39m[49m     """
[0m[49m[39m  110, 102[0m:[39m[49m     Check that the verification image contains exactly one face with
[0m[49m[39m  111, 103[0m:[39m[49m     acceptable quality metrics.
[0m[49m[39m  112, 104[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  113, 105[0m:[39m[49m     Why exactly one face? If there are zero faces, the image is useless.
[0m[49m[39m  114, 106[0m:[39m[49m     If there are multiple faces, we don't know which one is the patient.
[0m[49m[39m  115, 107[0m:[39m[49m     Both cases require a retake.
[0m[49m[39m  116, 108[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  117, 109[0m:[39m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[39m  118, 110[0m:[39m[49m         bucket: S3 bucket containing the verification image
[0m[49m[39m  119, 111[0m:[39m[49m         key: S3 object key for the verification image
[0m[49m[39m  120, 112[0m:[39m[49m 
