[0m[49m[39m  166, 158[0m:[39m[49m ## Step 2: Compare Faces
[0m[49m[39m  167, 159[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 168     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m *This is the core of the verification. We compare the check-in photo against the patient's enrolled reference photo. Rekognition does the heavy lifting: it extracts face embeddings (128-dimensional vectors representing facial geometry) and computes similarity.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `compare_faces`. This is the core of the verification. We compare the check-in photo against the patient's enrolled reference photo. Rekognition does the heavy lifting: it extracts face embeddings (128-dimensional vectors representing facial geometry) and computes similarity.*
[0m[49m[39m  169, 161[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  170, 162[0m:[39m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[39m  171, 163[0m:[39m[49m def compare_faces(source_bucket: str, source_key: str,
[0m[49m[39m  172, 164[0m:[39m[49m                   target_bucket: str, target_key: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[39m  173, 165[0m:[39m[49m     """
[0m[49m[39m  174, 166[0m:[39m[49m     Compare two face images and return a similarity score.
[0m[49m[39m  175, 167[0m:[39m[49m 
